claim.claim-text:
A method implemented in a computing infrastructure (10), comprising:
initiating (600) a user session with a remote server (12);
the remote server (12) allocating (605) for the user session a user ID for an initiating user (60) and a group ID for one or more additional users selectable by the initiating user (60);
selecting content for supply to the initiating user (60) and to said one or more additional users (60);
the remote server (12) causing the content to be stored in a control repository (22A, 22B);
the remote server (12) controlling (610) supply of the content according to the allocated ID such that all users can share (625) the content under the group ID but only the initiating user can change the content under the user ID;
the remote server (12) causing streaming of the content which comprises at least one of music and video from the control repository to the initiating user and the one or more additional users on separate computing devices within the user session; and
providing video chatting (615) amongst the initiating user (60) and the one or more additional users (60) on the separate computing devices, within the session, at the same time as the streaming.
